  "verdict": "FAIL_NOISE_UNIVERSALITY_AUDIT",
  "logical_conclusion": "Matching innovation mean and variance fixes the stationary mean and variance of the affine q process but not its higher cumulants, effective score, or standardized transition-kernel statistics. Independent coarse-graining produces strong Gaussian universality for light-tailed laws with controlled exponential moments. That universality fails as a statement about Q_lambda for Student-t tails, whose moment-generating function is infinite, and it can be blocked by shared non-Gaussian dependence. The RZS noise law is therefore macroscopically dispensable only under additional tail and dependence conditions that are not yet derived.",
